  "primaryContentSections" : [
    {
      "content" : [
        {
          "anchor" : "overview",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Overview",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "In the currently standardized form widely supported by browsers and other hosts, WebAssembly",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "is a 32-bit architecture. You have to take this into account when porting code from other",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "platforms, since ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Int",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " type is a signed 32-bit integer, and ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "UInt",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " is an unsigned 32-bit integer",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "when building with Wasm. You’ll need to audit codepaths that cast 64-bit integers to ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Int",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "or ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "UInt",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", and a good amount of cross-platform test coverage can help with that.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Additionally, there are differences in APIs exposed by the standard C library and Swift core",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "libraries which we discuss in the next few subsections.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "WASILibc-module",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "`WASILibc` module",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "When porting existing projects from other platforms to Wasm you might stumble upon code that",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "relies on importing a platform-specific ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/C_standard_library",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " module directly. It looks like ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "import Glibc",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " on Linux, or ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "import Darwin",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " on Apple platforms. Fortunately, most of the standard C library",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "APIs are available when using Swift for Wasm, you just need to use ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "import WASILibc",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " to get access to it.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "You will most likely want to preserve compatibility with other platforms, thus your imports would look",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "like this:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "#if canImport(Darwin)",
            "import Darwin",
            "#elseif canImport(Glibc)",
            "import Glibc",
            "#elseif canImport(WASILibc)",
            "import WASILibc",
            "#endif"
          ],
          "syntax" : "swift",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Limitations",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Limitations",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "WebAssembly and ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "https:\/\/wasi.dev\/",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " provide a constrained environment. Multi-threading, for example,",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "is an experimental feature and is only supported in development snapshots from the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "main",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " branch. Please be aware of these limitations when",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "porting your code, which also has an impact on what can be supported in the Swift",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "Foundation library.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Swift-Foundation-and-Dispatch",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Swift Foundation and Dispatch",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "identifier" : "https:\/\/swift.org\/core-libraries\/#foundation",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " is available in",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "Wasm, but in a limited capacity. The main reason is that ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "https:\/\/swift.org\/core-libraries\/#libdispatch",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " is unavailable, as it relies heavily on multi-threading support",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "that is still experimental in Swift for WebAssembly. Many Foundation APIs rely on the presence of Dispatch under the hood. A few other types are unavailable in browsers",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "or aren’t standardized in WASI hosts, such as support for sockets and low-level networking,",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "and they had to be disabled. These types are therefore absent in Foundation for Wasm:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
